# Walkthrough - GRAVITYFREE MVP Website

We have successfully built the MVP (Minimum Viable Product) for GRAVITYFREE SPORTS, focusing on **Structure, Copy, and B2B Lead Generation**.

## Key Achievements

### 1. Main Landing Page ([index.html](file:///c:/Users/gravi/catchbat01%20Dropbox/PARK%20SEONGSOO/PC/Desktop/antigravity/index.html))
- **Strategic Copywriting**: Used the "Data over Intuition" theme. Updated the Hero to highlight "10 years of craftsmanship" and "completion through data".
- **Minimalist Motion V Section**: A high-end white/black section focusing on the device's visual impact and domestic technical superiority.
- **Problem-Agitation-Solution (PAS) Flow**: Highlights the dangers of intuition-based training and offers data as the fix.

### 2. Product Detail Pages (`products/`)
- **[Motion V](file:///c:/Users/gravi/catchbat01%20Dropbox/PARK%20SEONGSOO/PC/Desktop/antigravity/products/motion-v.html)**: Focusing on ground reaction & kinematics.
- **[GSG (Garmin Swing Gauge)](file:///c:/Users/gravi/catchbat01%20Dropbox/PARK%20SEONGSOO/PC/Desktop/antigravity/products/gsg.html)**: Highlighting Garmin's global reliability vs. domestic AS benefits.
- **[G-Fit](file:///c:/Users/gravi/catchbat01%20Dropbox/PARK%20SEONGSOO/PC/Desktop/antigravity/products/g-fit.html)**: Focusing on kinetic chain and pneumatic resistance for athletes.

### 3. B2B Optimized Contact Form ([contact.html](file:///c:/Users/gravi/catchbat01%20Dropbox/PARK%20SEONGSOO/PC/Desktop/antigravity/contact.html))
- **Lead Generation Focus**: Fields designed for "Training Centers/Teams/Academies".
- **Data Capture**: Includes company name, role, athlete scale, and interest level to qualify leads immediately.

### 4. Visual Identity & Placeholders
- **Premium Dark Mode**: Used Electric Blue and Neon Lime for a high-performance tech feel.
- **Smart Placeholders**: Used structured CSS placeholders where images weren't provided, ensuring the layout remains professional for review.

